BILLIE ETHEL HARK et al. v. TONY GREEN et al. [No. 28,

January Term, 1935]

Decided May 2nd, 1935.

The cause was argued before Bond, C. J., Offutt, Parke, Sloan, Shehan, and Johnson, JJ.

Leonard Weinberg and Harry J. Green, with whom were Weinberg & Sweeten, on the brief, for the appellants. W. A. C. Hughes, Jr., with whom was Warner T. Mc-Guinn on the brief, for the appellees.

The opinion was delivered per Curiam.
